# Handover (CAIsat)

## Session start

1. Read `.cursor/rules/handover-notes.mdc` before other work (local-only, gitignored; bootstrap from `~/.cursor/rule-templates/handover.mdc` if missing).
2. If `.cursor/hooks/pending-handoff.md` exists, follow the **Context nearly full** flow in the full protocol (ask stop_work / finish_first / custom before continuing).
3. Confirm notes read in your first substantive reply (1–2 sentences).

## Context compaction

Triggers: `preCompact` hook, `pending-handoff.md`, resume-from-summary, or user asking about context limits. Full protocol: `~/.cursor/rule-templates/handover.mdc`.

Install/update global hooks: `bash ~/.cursor/rule-templates/context-compaction-hooks/scripts/install-cursor.sh`

Per-project checkpoints: `.cursor/hooks/pending-handoff.md`, `.cursor/hooks/last-compaction.txt` (gitignored).

## Session end

Post a brief 4-part handoff (Done, Remaining, Flags, Notes status). Update local `handover-notes.mdc` when facts or open items changed (do not commit it).
